    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Directional Bulb Remove and Replace</title>
        <para>The directional bulbs are located within the headlight module on the underside of the fender assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="g47006135">Figure 135, Item 1</hotlnk>. To replace the headlight halogen bulb or the amber
            directional bulb, the hood must be tilted.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unlatch the hood assembly and tilt the hood to the open position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the outboard socket cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006137">Figure 137, Item 1</hotlnk>); this will be the directional socket on each
                side of the chassis.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006135" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006135.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 135. Directional Light Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. REFLECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DIRECTIONAL BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT - DIRECTIONAL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Twist the socket cover to (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006136">Figure 136, Item 1</hotlnk>) remove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006136" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006136.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 136. Directional Bulb Access</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BULB AND SOCKET ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the socket and bulb assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006136">Figure 136, Item 2</hotlnk>), twist and pull up to remove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006137" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006137.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 137. Directional Bulb Remove / Install</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. AMBER DIRECTIONAL BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BULB SOCKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006138">Figure 138, Item 1</hotlnk>) or install directional bulb, push downward on
                bulb, twist and lift out (
                <hotlnk xrefid="g47006139">Figure 139, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Installation of directional bulb: insert bulb in socket, push down and twist to lock.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert bulb and socket assembly in light housing and twist to lock bulb in socket seat.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace socket cover and twist to lock.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006138" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006138.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 138. Directional Bulb Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DIRECTIONAL AMBER BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. DIRECTION BULB SOCKET AND SEAT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f47006139" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006139.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 139. Directional Bulb Replacement</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. AMBER BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BULB SOCKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HOUSING BASE AND WIRE CONNECTION</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
